adjectives.description: debauched (comparative more debauched, superlative most debauched)

entries.meaning: Indulging in or characterised by sensual pleasures to a degree perceived to be morally harmful; corrupted; immoral; self-indulgent.
examples: He was a man made for the exteremes of life; from the most debauched of men he had become the most ascetic.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of debauch
